<section name="Registry Management Commands" id="RegCommands">

<subsection name="Create Registry Index" id="CreateReg">
<p>
To create registry index in Elasticsearch run <i>create-registry</i> command.
</p>

<source>
Usage: registry-manager create-registry &lt;options&gt;

Create registry index

Optional parameters:
  -auth &lt;file&gt;         Authentication config file
  -es &lt;url&gt;            Elasticsearch URL. Default is http://localhost:9200
  -index &lt;name&gt;        Elasticsearch index name. Default is 'registry'
  -schema &lt;path&gt;       Elasticsearch index schema (JSON file)
                       Default value is $REGISTRY_MANAGER_HOME/elastic/registry.json
  -shards &lt;number&gt;     Number of shards (partitions) for registry index. Default is 1
  -replicas &lt;number&gt;   Number of replicas (extra copies) of registry index. Default is 0
</source>

</subsection>

<!-- ======================================================================= -->

<subsection name="Delete Registry Index" id="DeleteReg">
<p>
To delete registry index from Elasticsearch run <i>delete-registry</i> command.
</p>

<source>
Usage: registry-manager delete-registry &lt;options&gt;

Delete registry index and all its data

Optional parameters:
  -auth &lt;file&gt;    Authentication config file
  -es &lt;url&gt;       Elasticsearch URL. Default is http://localhost:9200
  -index &lt;name&gt;   Elasticsearch index name. Default is 'registry'
</source>

</subsection>

<!-- ======================================================================= -->

<subsection name="Update Registry schema" id="UpdateSchema">
<p>
To update Elasticsearch schema from a PDS data dictionary, run <i>update-schema</i> command:
</p>

<p>
<source>
Usage: registry-manager update-schema &lt;options&gt;

Update Elasticsearch schema

Required parameters:
  -file &lt;path&gt;     A file with a list of field names
Optional parameters:
  -auth &lt;file&gt;     Authentication config file
  -es &lt;url&gt;        Elasticsearch URL. Default is http://localhost:9200
  -index &lt;name&gt;    Elasticsearch index name. Default is 'registry'
</source>
</p>

<p>
This command is described in <a href="reg-custom.html">Registry Customization</a> section.
</p>

</subsection>

